PLib 6.1.6
Documentation : https://github.com/x3hy/plib/wiki
-------------------------
PLib is a C library made to make parsing command line arguments easier.
The Latest version of plib uses zero memory allocation and is a completely
header-only library which makes compilation a breeze.

Features:
- Header only library 
- Roughly ~400 lines of code.
- Completly static allocation.
- Optimized for user control.
- Very simple usage and installation.
- Extensive Error handling

--------------------------
Download/Install: 
You only require the plib6.h file which you can download locally
like so:

Edge:
wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/x3hy/plib/refs/heads/main/plib6.h

Stable:
wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/x3hy/plib/refs/tags/6.1.6/plib6.h

--------------------------

You can read through example.c for a quickstart template. and you can 
read the full documentation that the wiki link in the header.

--------------------------

